{"data":[{"id":"QLv0ozLRmKV-1","text":"In this American English pronunciation video, we're going to go over the pronunciation of","type":"sentence","start_time":"00:00:00.380","end_time":"00:00:05.090","unapproved":1,"translation":{"text":"Trong video phát âm tiếng Anh Mỹ này, chúng ta sẽ xem xét cách phát âm của","google_translate":1},"recordStat":{"voice_text":"","voice_audio":"","right":0,"wrong":0}},{"id":"QLv0ozLRmKV-2","text":"T and D between two consonants.","type":"sentence","start_time":"00:00:05.090","end_time":"00:00:15.639","unapproved":1,"translation":{"text":"T và D giữa hai phụ âm.","google_translate":1},"recordStat":{"voice_text":"","voice_audio":"","right":0,"wrong":0}},{"id":"QLv0ozLRmKV-3","text":"When the T and D sounds come between two other consonant sounds, many Americans will drop","type":"sentence","start_time":"00:00:15.639","end_time":"00:00:21.529","unapproved":1,"translation":{"text":"Khi âm T và D nằm giữa hai âm phụ âm khác, nhiều người Mỹ sẽ bỏ","google_translate":1},"recordStat":{"voice_text":"","voice_audio":"","right":0,"wrong":0}},{"id":"QLv0ozLRmKV-4","text":"them.","type":"sentence","start_time":"00:00:21.529","end_time":"00:00:22.529","unapproved":1,"translation":{"text":"họ","google_translate":1},"recordStat":{"voice_text":"","voice_audio":"","right":0,"wrong":0}},{"id":"QLv0ozLRmKV-5","text":"You can do it too.","type":"sentence","start_time":"00:00:22.529","end_time":"00:00:23.920","unapproved":1,"translation":{"text":"Bạn cũng có thể làm điều đó.","google_translate":1},"recordStat":{"voice_text":"","voice_audio":"","right":0,"wrong":0}},{"id":"QLv0ozLRmKV-6","text":"It might make words easier to pronounce and link, and smooth out your speech.","type":"sentence","start_time":"00:00:23.920","end_time":"00:00:28.400","unapproved":1,"translation":{"text":"Nó có thể làm cho các từ dễ phát âm và liên kết hơn, và làm mượt bài phát biểu của bạn.","google_translate":1},"recordStat":{"voice_text":"","voice_audio":"","right":0,"wrong":0}},{"id":"QLv0ozLRmKV-7","text":"Let's look at several examples.","type":"sentence","start_time":"00:00:28.400","end_time":"00:00:30.220","unapproved":1,"translation":{"text":"Hãy xem xét một vài ví dụ.","google_translate":1},"recordStat":{"voice_text":"","voice_audio":"","right":0,"wrong":0}},{"id":"QLv0ozLRmKV-8","text":"First, exactly.","type":"sentence","start_time":"00:00:30.220","end_time":"00:00:31.909","unapproved":1,"translation":{"text":"Đầu tiên, chính xác.","google_translate":1},"recordStat":{"voice_text":"","voice_audio":"","right":0,"wrong":0}},{"id":"QLv0ozLRmKV-9","text":"I get requests for this word quite a bit.","type":"sentence","start_time":"00:00:31.909","end_time":"00:00:36.040","unapproved":1,"translation":{"text":"Tôi nhận được yêu cầu cho từ này khá nhiều.","google_translate":1},"recordStat":{"voice_text":"","voice_audio":"","right":0,"wrong":0}},{"id":"QLv0ozLRmKV-10","text":"When we have the word 'exact', we will make a True T because it's part of an ending consonant","type":"sentence","start_time":"00:00:36.040","end_time":"00:00:41.930","unapproved":1,"translation":{"text":"Khi chúng ta có từ 'chính xác', chúng ta sẽ tạo ra một chữ T thật vì đó là một phần của phụ âm kết thúc","google_translate":1},"recordStat":{"voice_text":"","voice_audio":"","right":0,"wrong":0}},{"id":"QLv0ozLRmKV-11","text":"cluster.","type":"sentence","start_time":"00:00:41.930","end_time":"00:00:43.080","unapproved":1,"translation":{"text":"cụm.","google_translate":1},"recordStat":{"voice_text":"","voice_audio":"","right":0,"wrong":0}},{"id":"QLv0ozLRmKV-12","text":"Exact, tt, tt.","type":"sentence","start_time":"00:00:43.080","end_time":"00:00:46.560","unapproved":1,"translation":{"text":"Chính xác, tt, tt.","google_translate":1},"recordStat":{"voice_text":"","voice_audio":"","right":0,"wrong":0}},{"id":"QLv0ozLRmKV-13","text":"But when we add the -ly ending, it now comes between two consonants.","type":"sentence","start_time":"00:00:46.560","end_time":"00:00:50.310","unapproved":1,"translation":{"text":"Nhưng khi chúng ta thêm kết thúc -ly, bây giờ nó xuất hiện giữa hai phụ âm.","google_translate":1},"recordStat":{"voice_text":"","voice_audio":"","right":0,"wrong":0}},{"id":"QLv0ozLRmKV-14","text":"You'll hear a lot of native speakers say 'exactly', with no T sound.","type":"sentence","start_time":"00:00:50.310","end_time":"00:00:56.010","unapproved":1,"translation":{"text":"Bạn sẽ nghe rất nhiều người bản ngữ nói 'chính xác', không có âm T.","google_translate":1},"recordStat":{"voice_text":"","voice_audio":"","right":0,"wrong":0}},{"id":"QLv0ozLRmKV-15","text":"Exactly, exactly.","type":"sentence","start_time":"00:00:56.010","end_time":"00:00:57.560","unapproved":1,"translation":{"text":"Chính xác chính xác.","google_translate":1},"recordStat":{"voice_text":"","voice_audio":"","right":0,"wrong":0}},{"id":"QLv0ozLRmKV-16","text":"Almost no one will say 'exactly', with a True T. Exactly.","type":"sentence","start_time":"00:00:57.560","end_time":"00:01:03.610","unapproved":1,"translation":{"text":"Hầu như không ai sẽ nói 'chính xác', với một chữ T. chính xác.","google_translate":1},"recordStat":{"voice_text":"","voice_audio":"","right":0,"wrong":0}},{"id":"QLv0ozLRmKV-17","text":"This happens a lot when we link words.","type":"sentence","start_time":"00:01:03.610","end_time":"00:01:06.060","unapproved":1,"translation":{"text":"Điều này xảy ra rất nhiều khi chúng ta liên kết các từ.","google_translate":1},"recordStat":{"voice_text":"","voice_audio":"","right":0,"wrong":0}},{"id":"QLv0ozLRmKV-18","text":"Take, for example, the phrase 'grand piano'.","type":"sentence","start_time":"00:01:06.060","end_time":"00:01:09.780","unapproved":1,"translation":{"text":"Lấy ví dụ, cụm từ 'grand piano'.","google_translate":1},"recordStat":{"voice_text":"","voice_audio":"","right":0,"wrong":0}},{"id":"QLv0ozLRmKV-19","text":"The word 'grand', on its own or at the end of a sentence, grand, will usually have a","type":"sentence","start_time":"00:01:09.780","end_time":"00:01:15.869","unapproved":1,"translation":{"text":"Từ 'grand', tự nó hoặc ở cuối câu, grand, thường sẽ có một","google_translate":1},"recordStat":{"voice_text":"","voice_audio":"","right":0,"wrong":0}},{"id":"QLv0ozLRmKV-20","text":"light D release.","type":"sentence","start_time":"00:01:15.869","end_time":"00:01:17.840","unapproved":1,"translation":{"text":"phát hành ánh sáng D.","google_translate":1},"recordStat":{"voice_text":"","voice_audio":"","right":0,"wrong":0}},{"id":"QLv0ozLRmKV-21","text":"Grand, dd, dd.","type":"sentence","start_time":"00:01:17.840","end_time":"00:01:21.020","unapproved":1,"translation":{"text":"Cháu, đ, dd.","google_translate":1},"recordStat":{"voice_text":"","voice_audio":"","right":0,"wrong":0}},{"id":"QLv0ozLRmKV-22","text":"But when it's not the last word and the next word begins with a consonant, most people","type":"sentence","start_time":"00:01:21.020","end_time":"00:01:25.600","unapproved":1,"translation":{"text":"Nhưng khi đó không phải là từ cuối cùng và từ tiếp theo bắt đầu bằng một phụ âm, hầu hết mọi người","google_translate":1},"recordStat":{"voice_text":"","voice_audio":"","right":0,"wrong":0}},{"id":"QLv0ozLRmKV-23","text":"will drop that D. So, \"grand piano\" becomes \"gran' piano\".","type":"sentence","start_time":"00:01:25.600","end_time":"00:01:31.520","unapproved":1,"translation":{"text":"sẽ bỏ D. Vì vậy, \"grand piano\" trở thành \"gran 'piano\".","google_translate":1},"recordStat":{"voice_text":"","voice_audio":"","right":0,"wrong":0}},{"id":"QLv0ozLRmKV-24","text":"Grand piano, no D. Grand piano.","type":"sentence","start_time":"00:01:31.520","end_time":"00:01:36.450","unapproved":1,"translation":{"text":"Đại dương cầm, không D. Đại dương cầm.","google_translate":1},"recordStat":{"voice_text":"","voice_audio":"","right":0,"wrong":0}},{"id":"QLv0ozLRmKV-25","text":"Grand theft auto.","type":"sentence","start_time":"00:01:36.450","end_time":"00:01:38.759","unapproved":1,"translation":{"text":"Trộm cắp ô tô lớn.","google_translate":1},"recordStat":{"voice_text":"","voice_audio":"","right":0,"wrong":0}},{"id":"QLv0ozLRmKV-26","text":"Just one more.","type":"sentence","start_time":"00:01:38.759","end_time":"00:01:40.139","unapproved":1,"translation":{"text":"Chỉ một cái nữa thôi.","google_translate":1},"recordStat":{"voice_text":"","voice_audio":"","right":0,"wrong":0}},{"id":"QLv0ozLRmKV-27","text":"Probably not 'just one more'.","type":"sentence","start_time":"00:01:40.139","end_time":"00:01:42.649","unapproved":1,"translation":{"text":"Có lẽ không phải \"chỉ một nữa\".","google_translate":1},"recordStat":{"voice_text":"","voice_audio":"","right":0,"wrong":0}},{"id":"QLv0ozLRmKV-28","text":"Now, the word 'one' begins with a vowel letter, but the first sound is the W consonant.","type":"sentence","start_time":"00:01:42.649","end_time":"00:01:49.240","unapproved":1,"translation":{"text":"Bây giờ, từ 'một' bắt đầu bằng một chữ cái nguyên âm, nhưng âm đầu tiên là phụ âm W.","google_translate":1},"recordStat":{"voice_text":"","voice_audio":"","right":0,"wrong":0}},{"id":"QLv0ozLRmKV-29","text":"Just one more.","type":"sentence","start_time":"00:01:49.240","end_time":"00:01:50.850","unapproved":1,"translation":{"text":"Chỉ một cái nữa thôi.","google_translate":1},"recordStat":{"voice_text":"","voice_audio":"","right":0,"wrong":0}},{"id":"QLv0ozLRmKV-30","text":"Just once.","type":"sentence","start_time":"00:01:50.850","end_time":"00:01:52.479","unapproved":1,"translation":{"text":"Chỉ một lần.","google_translate":1},"recordStat":{"voice_text":"","voice_audio":"","right":0,"wrong":0}},{"id":"QLv0ozLRmKV-31","text":"Just for you.","type":"sentence","start_time":"00:01:52.479","end_time":"00:01:53.889","unapproved":1,"translation":{"text":"Chỉ dành cho bạn.","google_translate":1},"recordStat":{"voice_text":"","voice_audio":"","right":0,"wrong":0}},{"id":"QLv0ozLRmKV-32","text":"Must be funny.","type":"sentence","start_time":"00:01:53.889","end_time":"00:01:55.680","unapproved":1,"translation":{"text":"Cần trở nên hài hước.","google_translate":1},"recordStat":{"voice_text":"","voice_audio":"","right":0,"wrong":0}},{"id":"QLv0ozLRmKV-33","text":"Must be.","type":"sentence","start_time":"00:01:55.680","end_time":"00:01:56.779","unapproved":1,"translation":{"text":"Cần phải.","google_translate":1},"recordStat":{"voice_text":"","voice_audio":"","right":0,"wrong":0}},{"id":"QLv0ozLRmKV-34","text":"Probably not 'must be'.","type":"sentence","start_time":"00:01:56.779","end_time":"00:01:59.369","unapproved":1,"translation":{"text":"Có lẽ không \"phải\".","google_translate":1},"recordStat":{"voice_text":"","voice_audio":"","right":0,"wrong":0}},{"id":"QLv0ozLRmKV-35","text":"Must be funny.","type":"sentence","start_time":"00:01:59.369","end_time":"00:02:01.039","unapproved":1,"translation":{"text":"Cần trở nên hài hước.","google_translate":1},"recordStat":{"voice_text":"","voice_audio":"","right":0,"wrong":0}},{"id":"QLv0ozLRmKV-36","text":"Must be nice.","type":"sentence","start_time":"00:02:01.039","end_time":"00:02:02.920","unapproved":1,"translation":{"text":"Phải tốt đẹp.","google_translate":1},"recordStat":{"voice_text":"","voice_audio":"","right":0,"wrong":0}},{"id":"QLv0ozLRmKV-37","text":"Stand for.","type":"sentence","start_time":"00:02:02.920","end_time":"00:02:04.029","unapproved":1,"translation":{"text":"Là viết tắt của.","google_translate":1},"recordStat":{"voice_text":"","voice_audio":"","right":0,"wrong":0}},{"id":"QLv0ozLRmKV-38","text":"What does it stand for?","type":"sentence","start_time":"00:02:04.029","end_time":"00:02:06.689","unapproved":1,"translation":{"text":"nó đứng để làm gì?","google_translate":1},"recordStat":{"voice_text":"","voice_audio":"","right":0,"wrong":0}},{"id":"QLv0ozLRmKV-39","text":"Stand for.","type":"sentence","start_time":"00:02:06.689","end_time":"00:02:07.689","unapproved":1,"translation":{"text":"Là viết tắt của.","google_translate":1},"recordStat":{"voice_text":"","voice_audio":"","right":0,"wrong":0}},{"id":"QLv0ozLRmKV-40","text":"Probably not 'stand for'.","type":"sentence","start_time":"00:02:07.689","end_time":"00:02:10.860","unapproved":1,"translation":{"text":"Có lẽ không 'đứng cho'.","google_translate":1},"recordStat":{"voice_text":"","voice_audio":"","right":0,"wrong":0}},{"id":"QLv0ozLRmKV-41","text":"Stand for.","type":"sentence","start_time":"00:02:10.860","end_time":"00:02:11.890","unapproved":1,"translation":{"text":"Là viết tắt của.","google_translate":1},"recordStat":{"voice_text":"","voice_audio":"","right":0,"wrong":0}},{"id":"QLv0ozLRmKV-42","text":"I often get questions relating to these situations.","type":"sentence","start_time":"00:02:11.890","end_time":"00:02:15.610","unapproved":1,"translation":{"text":"Tôi thường nhận được câu hỏi liên quan đến những tình huống này.","google_translate":1},"recordStat":{"voice_text":"","voice_audio":"","right":0,"wrong":0}},{"id":"QLv0ozLRmKV-43","text":"Dropping the T and D in these cases can help smooth out your speech, so try it out.","type":"sentence","start_time":"00:02:15.610","end_time":"00:02:21.390","unapproved":1,"translation":{"text":"Giảm T và D trong những trường hợp này có thể giúp làm dịu bài phát biểu của bạn, vì vậy hãy thử nó.","google_translate":1},"recordStat":{"voice_text":"","voice_audio":"","right":0,"wrong":0}},{"id":"QLv0ozLRmKV-44","text":"If you can think of other examples, put them in the comments below and use other people's","type":"sentence","start_time":"00:02:21.390","end_time":"00:02:26.250","unapproved":1,"translation":{"text":"Nếu bạn có thể nghĩ về các ví dụ khác, hãy đưa chúng vào các bình luận bên dưới và sử dụng người khác","google_translate":1},"recordStat":{"voice_text":"","voice_audio":"","right":0,"wrong":0}},{"id":"QLv0ozLRmKV-45","text":"examples to practice.","type":"sentence","start_time":"00:02:26.250","end_time":"00:02:28.690","unapproved":1,"translation":{"text":"ví dụ để thực hành.","google_translate":1},"recordStat":{"voice_text":"","voice_audio":"","right":0,"wrong":0}},{"id":"QLv0ozLRmKV-46","text":"That's it, and thanks so much for using Rachel's English.","type":"sentence","start_time":"00:02:28.690","end_time":"00:02:56.840","unapproved":1,"translation":{"text":"Đó là nó, và cảm ơn rất nhiều vì đã sử dụng tiếng Anh của Rachel.","google_translate":1},"recordStat":{"voice_text":"","voice_audio":"","right":0,"wrong":0}}],"view":"0","comment":"0","like":"0","dislike":"0","like_status":0,"is_news_a_minute":0,"slideshow":0,"id":"QLv0ozLRmKV","url":"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9upLVtyMdsQ","title":"How to Pronounce T and D between Consonants -- American English","thumbnail":"https://i.ytimg.com/vi/9upLVtyMdsQ/hqdefault.jpg","mp4":0,"comment_id":null,"duration":"00:02:59","is_new":null}